#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:315
msgid "Since our query contains all the fields in the `Film` class we will retrieve all the fields in our response. Since GraphQL API responses are client determined, the client can choose which fields it will require."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:319
msgid "Let's assume that our client only requires `title` and `releaseDate` making the previous call to the API `Over-fetching` of unnecessary data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:321
msgid "Enter the following query into GraphiQL and hit the `play` button:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"query allFilms {\n"
"  allFilms {\n"
"    title\n"
"    releaseDate\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:334
msgid "Notice in the response we have only retrieved the required fields.  Therefore, we have prevented `Over-fetching`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:337
msgid "Let's continue to expand our GraphQL API by adding the following to the `FilmResource` class."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:345
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Query\n"
"    @Description(\"Get a Films from a galaxy far far away\")\n"
"    public Film getFilm(@Name(\"filmId\") int id) {\n"
"        return service.getFilm(id);\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:350
msgid "Notice how we have excluded the value in the `@Query` annotation.  Therefore, the name of the query is implicitly set as the method name excluding the `get`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:353
msgid "This query will allow the client to retrieve the film by id, and the `@Name` annotation on the parameter changes the parameter name to `filmId` rather than the default `id` that it would be if you omit the `@Name` annotation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:355
msgid "Enter the following into `GraphiQL` and make a request."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:366
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"query getFilm {\n"
"  film(filmId: 1) {\n"
"    title\n"
"    director\n"
"    releaseDate\n"
"    episodeID\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:371
msgid "The `film` query method requested fields can be determined as such in our previous example. This way we can retrieve individual film information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:375
msgid "However, say our client requires both films with filmId `0` and `1`.  In a REST API the client would have to make two calls to the API.  Therefore, the client would be `Under-fetching`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:377
msgid "In GraphQL it is possible to make multiple queries at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:379
msgid "Enter the following into GraphiQL to retrieve two films:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:396
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:503
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"query getFilms {\n"
"  film0: film(filmId: 0) {\n"
"    title\n"
"    director\n"
"    releaseDate\n"
"    episodeID\n"
"  }\n"
"  film1: film(filmId: 1) {\n"
"    title\n"
"    director\n"
"    releaseDate\n"
"    episodeID\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:399
msgid "This enabled the client to fetch the required data in a single request."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Expanding the API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:404
msgid "Until now, we have created a GraphQL API to retrieve film data.  We now want to enable the clients to retrieve the `Hero` data of the `Film`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:406
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:512
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:622
msgid "Add the following to our `FilmResource` class:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:412
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    public List<Hero> heroes(@Source Film film) { // <1>\n"
"        return service.getHeroesByFilm(film);\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:415
msgid "Enable `List<Hero>` data to be added to queries that respond with `Film`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:419
msgid "By adding this method we have effectively changed the schema of the GraphQL API.  Although the schema has changed the previous queries will still work.  Since we only expanded the API to be able to retrieve the `Hero` data of the `Film`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:421
msgid "Enter the following into GraphiQL to retrieve the film and hero data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:439
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"query getFilmHeroes {\n"
"  film(filmId: 1) {\n"
"    title\n"
"    director\n"
"    releaseDate\n"
"    episodeID\n"
"    heroes {\n"
"      name\n"
"      height\n"
"      mass\n"
"      darkSide\n"
"      lightSaber\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:442
msgid "The response now includes the heroes of the film."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "Batching"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:447
msgid "When you are exposing a `Collection` return like our `getAllFilms`, you might want to use the batch form of the above, to more efficiently fetch the heroes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:453
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    public List<List<Hero>> heroes(@Source List<Film> films) { // <1>\n"
"        // Here fetch all hero lists\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:456
msgid "Here receive the films as a batch, allowing you to fetch the corresponding heroes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:457
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reactive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:460
msgid "Queries can be made reactive by using `Uni`, or `CompletionStage` as a return type, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Query\n"
"    @Description(\"Get a Films from a galaxy far far away\")\n"
"    public Uni<Film> getFilm(int filmId) {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:471
msgid "Due to the underlying library, graphql-java, `Uni` is creating a `CompletionStage` under the hood."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:473
msgid "Or you can use `CompletionStage`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Query\n"
"    @Description(\"Get a Films from a galaxy far far away\")\n"
"    public CompletionStage<Film> getFilm(int filmId) {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:484
msgid "Using `Uni` or `CompletionStage` means that when a request contains more than one query, they will be executed concurrently."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:486
msgid "For instance, the query below will fetch `film0` and `film1` concurrently:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:505
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mutations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:508
msgid "Mutations are used when data is created, updated or deleted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:510
msgid "Let's now add the ability to add and delete heroes to our GraphQL API."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:520
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Mutation\n"
"    public Hero createHero(Hero hero) {\n"
"        service.addHero(hero);\n"
"        return hero;\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:525
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Mutation\n"
"    public Hero deleteHero(int id) {\n"
"        return service.deleteHero(id);\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:528
msgid "Enter the following into `GraphiQL` to insert a `Hero`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:546
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mutation addHero {\n"
"  createHero(hero: {\n"
"      name: \"Han\",\n"
"      surname: \"Solo\"\n"
"      height: 1.85\n"
"      mass: 80\n"
"      darkSide: false\n"
"      episodeIds: [4, 5, 6]\n"
"  \t}\n"
"  )\n"
"  {\n"
"    name\n"
"    surname\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:549
msgid "By using this mutation we have created a `Hero` entity in our service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:554
msgid "Notice how in the response we have retrieved the `name` and `surname` of the created Hero. This is because we selected to retrieve these fields in the response within the `{ }` in the mutation query.  This can easily be a server side generated field that the client may require."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:556
msgid "Let's now try deleting an entry:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:565
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mutation DeleteHero {\n"
"  deleteHero(id :3){\n"
"    name\n"
"    surname\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:569
msgid "Similar to the `createHero` mutation method we also retrieve the `name` and `surname` of the hero we have deleted which is defined in `{ }`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:570
#, no-wrap
msgid "Subscriptions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:573
msgid "Subscriptions allows you to subscribe to a query. It allows you to receive events."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:575
msgid "Subscription is currently still considered experimental."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:577
msgid "Example: We want to know when new Heroes are being created:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "    BroadcastProcessor<Hero> processor = BroadcastProcessor.create(); // <1>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:589
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Mutation\n"
"    public Hero createHero(Hero hero) {\n"
"        service.addHero(hero);\n"
"        processor.onNext(hero); // <2>\n"
"        return hero;\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:594
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Subscription\n"
"    public Multi<Hero> heroCreated(){\n"
"        return processor; // <3>\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:598
msgid "The `Multi` processor that will broadcast any new Heros"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:599
msgid "When adding a new Hero, also broadcast it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:600
msgid "Make the stream available in the schema and as a WebSocket during runtime"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:603
msgid "Any client that now connect to the `/graphql` WebSocket connection will receive events on new Heroes being created:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:613
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"subscription ListenForNewHeroes {\n"
"  heroCreated {\n"
"    name\n"
"    surname\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:616
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating Queries by fields"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:620
msgid "Queries can also be done on individual fields. For example, let's create a method to query heroes by their last name."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:629
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    @Query\n"
"    public List<Hero> getHeroesWithSurname(@DefaultValue(\"Skywalker\") String surname) {\n"
"        return service.getHeroesBySurname(surname);\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:633
msgid "By using the `@DefaultValue` annotation we have determined that the surname value will be `Skywalker` when the parameter is not provided."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:635
msgid "Test the following queries with GraphiQL:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:652
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"query heroWithDefaultSurname {\n"
"  heroesWithSurname{\n"
"    name\n"
"    surname\n"
"    lightSaber\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"query heroWithSurnames {\n"
"  heroesWithSurname(surname: \"Vader\") {\n"
"    name\n"
"    surname\n"
"    lightSaber\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:654
#, no-wrap
msgid "Context"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:657
msgid "You can get information about the GraphQL request anywhere in your code, using this experimental, SmallRye specific feature:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: upstream/_versions/2.7/guides/smallrye-graphql.adoc:662
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@Inject\n"
"Context context;\n"
